[The gaussian model Ian Hancock mentions is really very old now. It
is hard to guess which model exactly , but it may well be Gloster's
model of the late 1970s/1980, as he states it is in Fortran. Better models
use the movement of bodies of air, "puff" models; gaussian models are
useful but very out of date.

Stress in animals awaiting slaughter, especially given the confusion and
inefficiencies reported in the UK press and the potential impacts on
virus production, should not be ignored.

As to any possible aerosols produced during farm cleaning and
disinfection, this is not a matter for discussion and legal statements, but
measurement. Mod.MJH/TG/JW
